data.message: I don't even pay attention to race anymore. White priviledge? Not my fault. I treat everybody the same, regardless of race/ethnicity. And I'm not going to be persecuted just because I'm white.

Oh fuck, I'm white! I must be racist! It's obviously my fault that racism exists! of course it doesn't matter that I do what I can to make people understand the painfully obvious idea that people are people regardless of color. Better start feeling that white guilt more often.

I'm not attacking him/her. I'm just saying it's pointless throwing blame around, and talking about privilege is kind of stupid in any context. What about all of out technological privilege? Should we feel guilty for having medicine that people in poorer areas of the world don't have? Or should we just try to give it to them? What about our temporal privilege? We don't live in the dark ages, and we should check that privilege. This comic itself is a product of "privilege" so it shouldn't have been written, same with this conversation, and this school, and literally everything else that exists. Also, I don't think the writer of this comic knows what institutionalized means.

Whoever made this post is trash. "White privilege" is nothing more than a made up tool to ignite racial tension and division among ethnicities so we all become good slave scum and bend over to Obama or whoever's in office. I hope the piece of garbage who made this post seriously evaluates his or her priorities.

That was probably the dumbest crap I've ever read in my life. If you know that the odds are stacked up against you, maybe you should work harder. Black people can't get anywhere cause they use up all their energy complaining about issues that hardly have an effect on whether they are successful or not. I'm not trying to attack whoever posted this, but I'm just not sure what this comic was trying to accomplish, other than providing new things for people to whine about.

I really couldn't care less about the whole debate, but whoever wrote the comic couldn't even spell "receive" correctly, so I'm thinking there might be a better resource if you really want to educate people about "white privilege." Just sayin'.

Obviously white privilege exists to some capacity, HOWEVER- this cartoon is an inaccurate and unsophisticated representation of the social problems occurring today with race. Secondly, why does the cartoon ignore Latinos, Asians, Jewish And Middle Eastern people? They comprise of roughly 45% of the country- this cartoon is an unrealistic, creates an "otherization" mentality with blacks v whites and is a  red herring. One should refrain from posting inaccuracies and irrelevant material if one wants to discuss socio-political matters.

I posted either this article or a similar one months ago and got around THIRTY comments from people agreeing and opposing the existence of white privilege. I think it is important for people to understand that privilege in many senses exist!

I think the problem with talking about white privilege is that it often seems like people are blaming all white people for the way those in a position of power treat others.
Guys, white privilege is real. It's not your fault if you have it, but it exists. You just have to use it to other's advantage when you can. Stand up for minorities who are being treated unfairly, because people will usually listen to a white person in that situation.
